cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with learning disentangled representations from pairs of non-i.i.d. images without requiring annotation of groups, individual factors, or the number of factors that have changed. This falls under the domain of machine learning and computer vision, which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE. Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories as the paper deals with learning representations and image observations.
